          "title": "Interactive sessions",
          "expandable": true,
          "defaultExpansion": true,
          "helpText": {
            "aws": "With AWS Glue, you only pay for usage. AWS Glue interactive sessions allow you to rapidly build, test, and run data preparation and analytics applications. There are no resources to manage, no upfront costs, and you are not charged for startup or shutdown time. You are charged an hourly rate based on the number of Data Processing Units (or DPUs) used in your Interactive Session. A single Data Processing Unit (DPU) provides 4 vCPU and 16 GB of memory. Minimum billing duration for each provisioned development endpoint is 1-minute.",
            "aws-cn": "With Amazon Glue, you only pay for usage. Amazon Glue interactive sessions allow you to rapidly build, test, and run data preparation and analytics applications. There are no resources to manage, no upfront costs, and you are not charged for startup or shutdown time. You are charged an hourly rate based on the number of Data Processing Units (or DPUs) used in your Interactive Session. A single Data Processing Unit (DPU) provides 4 vCPU and 16 GB of memory. Minimum billing duration for each provisioned development endpoint is 1-minute.",
            "aws-us-gov": "With AWS Glue, you only pay for usage. AWS Glue interactive sessions allow you to rapidly build, test, and run data preparation and analytics applications. There are no resources to manage, no upfront costs, and you are not charged for startup or shutdown time. You are charged an hourly rate based on the number of Data Processing Units (or DPUs) used in your Interactive Session. A single Data Processing Unit (DPU) provides 4 vCPU and 16 GB of memory. Minimum billing duration for each provisioned development endpoint is 1-minute."
          },
