          "title": "Development endpoints",
          "expandable": true,
          "defaultExpansion": false,
          "helpText": {
            "aws": "With AWS Glue, you only pay for usage. A development endpoint is an environment that you can use to develop and test your AWS Glue scripts. There are no resources to manage, no upfront costs, and you are not charged for startup or shutdown time. You are charged an hourly rate based on the number of Data Processing Units (or DPUs) used to run your ETL development endpoint. A single Data Processing Unit (DPU) provides 4 vCPU and 16 GB of memory. Minimum billing duration for each provisioned development endpoint is 10-minutes.",
            "aws-cn": "With Amazon Glue, you only pay for usage. A development endpoint is an environment that you can use to develop and test your Amazon Glue scripts. There are no resources to manage, no upfront costs, and you are not charged for startup or shutdown time. You are charged an hourly rate based on the number of Data Processing Units (or DPUs) used to run your ETL development endpoint. A single Data Processing Unit (DPU) provides 4 vCPU and 16 GB of memory. Minimum billing duration for each provisioned development endpoint is 10-minutes.",
